narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Great class and not too much work. Would definitely recommend it
If you care about Rwanda or the genocide, don't take it. You will be really disappointed. Take it only if you are a lazy senior and need an easy class to write your thesis in...

It's a great course, the assignments are varied and fascinating, the paper will challenge you and push you to think deeply about the subject. It can be lecture-ish at times however. Also, the quality of the seminar depends a lot on whether you do all the assigned reading, so definitely do that! You get what you put in!
